The paper deals with decision-making in decentralized environments, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of Q-value functions is a popular approach in reinforcement learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO) for decision-making. The paper also discusses the computation of policies, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
